                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18260406-140-off740 t18260406-140-crimeloc742"></join> - I had seen it safe about half an hour before I heard it was gone.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18260406-140-person797">
                  HENRY 
                  HUNT
               <interp inst="t18260406-140-person797" type="surname" value="HUNT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-140-person797" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18260406-140-person797" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I saw the prisoner, on the 6th of March, go into Mr. Smith's house with some matches, he asked if they would buy any - he came out, looked round the door and went in again three times - he then went in and came out with a bundle - I was in a house opposite - I ran out and called Mr. Smith, and asked if he had lost any thing - he said "Yes, my jacket;" I ran after the prisoner and he was taken - I had not lost sight of him - he threw the jacket on the ground.</p>
